The paper presents a source-to-source translation of C code into Eiffel, a modern object-oriented programming language, and discusses the challenges and solutions in handling the entire C language, including its usage of native system libraries and inlined assembly code. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and/or Programming Languages and Compilers (cs.PL) sub-categories.
